<TITLE> Wife and son of ex-state minister Ziaul Haque get 6 and 8 years </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 13 (bdnes24.com)- A Dhaka court Thursday convicted the wife and son of former state minister Ziaul Haque in separate tax evasion cases. Wife Nasima Haque will have to serve five years in jail, while son Mashfiqul Haque must serve eight years. The special court of judge Shamsun Nahar awarded two separate jail terms of five years and one year to Nasima, on separate charges of concealing wealth information and not paying income tax. Her sentences will run concurrently. The court also ordered confiscation of nine bhoris of gold ornaments kept by Nasima in a bank safety deposit box. Mashfiqul received sentences of five years and three years on similar charges, and will have to serve the total eight years as his sentences will run consecutively. As both the convicted are on the run their sentences will come into effete from day of their arrest. On Nov 29, Ziaul Haque, wife Nasima and son Mashfiqul were sentenced to a total of eight years' rigorous imprisonment also for tax evasion. bdnew
